<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Academy on Example Academy</title><link>https://meshery-extensions.github.io/meshery-academy/pr-preview/pr-94/</link><description>Recent content in Academy on Example Academy</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://meshery-extensions.github.io/meshery-academy/pr-preview/pr-94/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Certified Meshery Associate</title><link>https://meshery-extensions.github.io/meshery-academy/pr-preview/pr-94/certifications/c5ada327-8a58-4c8a-b9fa-51b95696488c/certified-meshery-associate/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://meshery-extensions.github.io/meshery-academy/pr-preview/pr-94/certifications/c5ada327-8a58-4c8a-b9fa-51b95696488c/certified-meshery-associate/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;This is the entry-level certification for professionals new to Meshery. It validates a candidate&amp;rsquo;s foundational knowledge of the platform&amp;rsquo;s core concepts.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Meshery CLI (mesheryctl) Contributor Exam</title><link>https://meshery-extensions.github.io/meshery-academy/pr-preview/pr-94/certifications/c5ada327-8a58-4c8a-b9fa-51b95696488c/certified-meshery-contributor/meshery-cli/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://meshery-extensions.github.io/meshery-academy/pr-preview/pr-94/certifications/c5ada327-8a58-4c8a-b9fa-51b95696488c/certified-meshery-contributor/meshery-cli/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;The Meshery CLI examination verifies contributor understanding of one of Meshery&amp;rsquo;s core architectural components and is one of a set of mandatory exams comprising the Certified Meshery Contributor certification.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This exam focuses on the candidate&amp;rsquo;s ability to contribute to the Meshery CLI codebase. The exam covers a variety of topics, including:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://docs.meshery.io/project/contributing/contributing-cli-guide"&gt;Meshery CLI Contributing Guidelines&lt;/a&gt; - Design principles and code conventions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://docs.meshery.io/project/contributing/contributing-cli"&gt;Contributing to Meshery CLI&lt;/a&gt; - How to contribute to Meshery Command Line Interface.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://docs.meshery.io/project/contributing/contributing-cli-tests"&gt;Contributing to Meshery CLI End-to-End Tests&lt;/a&gt; - How to contribute to Meshery Command Line Interface end-to-end testing with BATS.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This exam does not cover Meshery CLI usage. For information on using Meshery CLI, please refer to the following resources:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Content Formatting Examples</title><link>https://meshery-extensions.github.io/meshery-academy/pr-preview/pr-94/content-formatting-examples/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://meshery-extensions.github.io/meshery-academy/pr-preview/pr-94/content-formatting-examples/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Welcome! This page showcases examples of Hugo shortcodes, images, and Markdown.&lt;/p&gt;






